configure probes whether the shell maintains $LINENO; brush's was
frozen at 1 (a dynamic var reading the call frame's position that
NOTHING ever wrote), so every configure took the sed-rewrite-myself
fallback — the exact in-flight pipelines the user's stuck box showed.

- the interpreter records each statement's source position on the
  current call frame (complete-commands and compound-list items; AST
  spans already existed), via new call_stack_mut/current_frame_mut.
- the engine's script entries (brush_sh, the snooped nested sh) push
  a base command-string frame around the run — brush only pushed one
  in its own source_file path, so top-level scripts had NO frame and
  LINENO fell back to 1.

configure's exact eval/expr LINENO probe now passes; conformance
corpus grows a 'lineno' probe (39/39 vs bash). Full gate green.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
